Bolivian voices: Jaqi Aru, spreading Aymara on the internet
Aymara is a native American language and one of the official languages of Peru and Bolivia.
There are about two million speakers of Aymara in Bolivia and almost three million in total in South America.
Ruben Hilari, with some local volunteers from El Alto, Bolivia, established the virtual community Jaqi Aru.
The aim of the Jaqi Aru website is to highlight and disseminate the Aymara language on the internet, through the creation of content in digital media, which consists of translation, multimedia use and social media tools.
Aymara has been losing speakers, both due to the use of Spanish and Quechua in the past century and many of the speakers of Aymara now speak Quechua, another native South American language.
