"We Are Not Ants": A book that promotes informed optimism
"Where ignorance is happiness, it is madness to be wise", wrote Thomas Gray in 1742.
In the age of social media and digital media, sometimes it seems that there is only bad news and there is nothing the average citizen can do about it.
Most people know the old saying that ignorance is happiness, but is it possible that it is exactly the opposite, that ignorance generates unhappiness?
The book We Are Not Ants came about in response to a widespread negativity and sense of powerlessness.
But it is not a simple self-help book, massive and carefree.
The four young Spanish authors, who combine knowledge of economics, journalism, international development, entrepreneurship, marketing and design, presented the project as a
If we were ants, humans would be a happy species.
We have colonized the entire planet, our life expectancy is increasing and our technological achievements are impressive.
However, we realize the magnitude of the challenges we face and the dangers and injustices that still lurk before us.
We are a community and what we do we do together, we share a common origin and, alongside planet Earth, we also share a common future.
A future that we decide.
The book is divided into three chapters:
Chapter 1
The world is fine.
Humans have made incredible progress in many areas over the past few decades: we live longer, we are able to feed more, we are able to educate more, we have eradicated many diseases that were once deadly, and we are more supportive.
Chapter 3
Many will say that this is not enough and that humans have not been able to solve the major social challenges.
But we're doing better than we think and than the pessimists want us to believe.
Chapter 3
What can you do to make it better?
Stop complaining!
The world is full of social innovators, people who create ideas and tools that allow us all to live better, more sustainable and with more opportunities for all without having to give up on progress.
If you want to know them and know what you can do to live up to your ideals, you'll find a selection of 120 in the book and more on that website.
We are not ants includes Global Voices in its selection of innovative platforms.
Through innovative use of infographics and a combination of traditional and digital media, We Are Not Ants provides a balanced and critical view of the state of the planet, and offers concrete alternatives to change.
The book can be previewed on the website and purchased on paper or in digital edition.
You can also visit the blog to learn about the latest news and ideas, and follow them on Twitter @NoSomosHormigas.
