Blogging Festival: Mexico - Citizenship, violence and blogs
Global Voices en Español has an interest in encouraging blogging and promoting blogger networks, and it has been thought that a good way to achieve this may be through the well-known "Blog Festivals".
In this way, while GV en Español would be helping to generate original content with a certain level of reflection and analysis, the participating bloggers would benefit from greater visibility of their work by being referenced on Global Voices.
But let's look at the details of the Festival:
Scope: Mexico
As the location and geographical area of our first Blog Festival in 2011, Mexico has been chosen, a great country that is going through a period of violence that never ceases.
Apart from that, in Mexico we have several collaborators who will support us in the dissemination of this virtual event.
While the largest number of bloggers, and the most well-known, are in Mexico City, we expect the participation of bloggers from cities like Guadalajara, Monterrey, Puebla, Toluca, Ciudad Juárez and others.
We even look forward to the participation of Mexican bloggers living outside their country.
We clarify that participation is not restricted to bloggers or blogs devoted exclusively to the topic indicated in the following paragraph, any blog and blogger can participate.
Subject: Citizenship, violence and blogs
In a context like the one described, there are always stories that don't show up in traditional media, stories that are examples of resilience that we should know about.
Is it advisable to regulate media coverage of violence if that is what readers, the media, NGOs or the government would do?
Are there tangible results of campaigns of activism (on the internet or not) against violence in Mexico?
Has the use of the internet affected the prevention or visibility of violent incidents given that not all of these incidents are published in traditional media?
Could or should new media go beyond coverage and reflection?
Participation:
Any Mexican blogger can participate by posting a post on the proposed topic on their own blog.
That post has to be original, that is, the blogger's own creation, not copied from another source.
The structure, style and extent of the post are left to the blogger's discretion.
It should be made clear that the approach to the subject is open.
It may be from some of the questions suggested or from what the blogger considers appropriate.
When the blogger has posted his post for the Festival, he must communicate it to this email: juan.arellano arroba globalvoicesonline punto org indicating the following:
Name of the author
Name of the blog
Title of the post
Permanent link or URL of the post.
There's a button available, the image of this post, for bloggers to use and put on their blogs as a sign of being involved.
Once you put the button on your blog you should refer to this post.
At the end of the participation period, the participants will be sorted and summarized for the purpose of publishing a compilation post on Global Voices.
Depending on the number of shares, posts may be cited or not, mainly for reasons of space.
Timeline: Activities to be carried out within the blog festival will be as follows:
From 29 July to 10 August.
- Period of participation.
August 1 to 10.
- Selection period and preparation of the summary post with the contributions made.
August 11 to 15.
- Publishing the summary post on Global Voices in Spanish.
An additional precision: This is not a contest, so there are no winners or losers.
It is a question of seeking input, collaboration and testimonies on the proposed subject, so as to be able to draw up a broad, varied and up-to-date picture on the subject.
Participation on Twitter
On this occasion we want the Festival to be present and active on Twitter, for which we put at the disposal of all tweeter the official hashtag of the Festival: #vocesmx
With this tag will be done all the work of dissemination and call to participate in the Festival, but we also wish that there are tweets alluding to the theme of the Festival with this hashtag.
We will follow you and a selection of the most interesting will be published in our summary post.
