The protesters, who did not react, tried to take justice into their own hands, and a fight broke out.
It was the excuse the police were hoping for.
At the first sign of conflict, tear gas and rubber bullets were thrown at the crowd.
Panic as people flee from the police Photo: Calé, authorized publication.
At no point was there any intention of invading the city hall, people have simply become furious and started to counterattack the police with stones and sticks.
What happened next was the biggest police abuse case of the decade: Special strike troops evacuated the streets of downtown Rio from the bohemian neighborhood of La Lapa, which is 2.5 km away.
In response, many shops and buildings were looted and robbed on President Vargas Avenue.
Police are passing through burning garbage cans, while some buildings are being attacked on President Vargas Avenue.
