Even after the conflict ended, police continued to throw tear gas at peaceful protesters returning home, far from the city hall.
There was no distinction between the agitators and the peaceful people trying to return home.
Since the subway was closed, people had to walk out of the conflict zone.
A street vendor tries to breathe after inhaling tear gas, while the police become indiscriminate in their attacks, throwing rubber bullets and tear gas at people.
