Photo: Calé, authorized release.
Many decided to leave the demonstration at the first sign of conflict, and went to the Lapa neighborhood to get a beer, a place they felt far away and safe.
But soon the police arrived and people got stuck in bars and restaurants as chaos swept the streets.
While people started insulting them, the police were also throwing tear gas at buildings irresponsibly.
Police are throwing tear gas at peaceful protesters waiting for the opening of the metro station.
Metro employees opened a side door for people to seek shelter, but ended up creating a funnel where people were trapped inhaling gas.
Below many were lying on the floor, nauseous.
Photo: Calé, authorized release.
Yes, there were vandals in the demonstration, who broke and burned things, but most of these acts happened in President Vargas, near the city hall.
In meetings and on social media people are now talking about their fear of going out into the streets to protest and some want the protests to end.
