Here are some reactions on Twitter:
You don't decide where we want our money to go.
We are.
We want our money for national development, social service and security.
Abolishing pigs.
If Noynoy and the protesters are on the same side, why did people still go to the streets after his press conference?
Abolish vs. change your name.
Pixel Offensive said that if the president is truly on the people's side against paying this fund, he should speak out on the following:
