Kulangot lang it is kumpara sa PORK nya.
2) Your staff would not tweet anything against the demonstrations.
This only exposes the way of thinking of the inner circle of the presidency.
Let's raise this discussion a little bit, shall we?
Do you expect a farmer president to serve the people?
Critics argue that this presidential corruption  consisting of single-payment allocations, whose disbursement remains solely at the discretion of the president and his executive department worth more than 1.3 billion pesos.
Hours before the anti-corruption rally, presidential spokeswoman Abigail Valte tweeted a link to an article describing outrage over this payment to campaign politicians as a "pleasant but out of place statement".
Are we thinking about the next step, like Juan Tamad, are we waiting for someone to solve our problem?
